Topic: Minimum Privilege Principle (PoLP) & Why Over-Permission is Dangerous
ğŸ“Œ What is the Principle of Least Privilege (PoLP)?

The Principle of Least Privilege states that a user, system, or process should have only the minimum permissions required to perform its task â€” nothing more.

This applies to:

Users

Applications

Services

Databases

Cloud resources

APIs

ğŸš¨ Why Over-Permission is a Serious Security Risk

Granting excessive permissions can lead to:

Privilege escalation

Lateral movement inside systems

Data breaches

Complete system compromise if one account is breached

Attackers donâ€™t need admin access initially â€” they exploit over-perissioned accounts.

ğŸ§  Real-World Example

